{{other places}} {{Infobox settlement | official_name = Taleqan | native_name = طالقان | settlement_type = City | image_skyline = Taleqan, iran.jpg | imagesize = | image_caption = | pushpin_map = Iran | mapsize = 150px | subdivision_type = [[List of countries|Country]] | subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces of Iran|Province]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Alborz Province|Alborz]] | subdivision_type2 = [[Counties of Iran|County]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Taleqan County|Taleqan]] | subdivision_type3 = [[Bakhsh]] | subdivision_name3 = [[Central District (Taleqan County)|Central]] | leader_title = | leader_name = | established_title = | established_date = | area_total_km2 = | area_footnotes = | population_as_of = 2016 Census | population_total = 3,545 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref> | population_density_km2 = auto | timezone = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]] | utc_offset = +3:30 | timezone_DST = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]] | utc_offset_DST = +4:30 | coordinates = {{coord|36|15|55|N|50|46|57|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}} | elevation_m = | area_code = | website = | footnotes = | name = }} '''Taleqan''' ({{lang-fa|طالقان}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Ṭâleqân''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|10038236}}</ref> is a city in the capital of [[Taleqan County]], [[Alborz Province]], [[Iran]].
It is located in the [[Alborz|Alborz mountain range]].
Native people from Taleqan speak [[Tati language (Iran)|Tati language]].
At the 2006 census, its population was 3,281, in 988 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|23}}</ref>
== History == The city of Taleqan consisted of four neighborhoods.
